{"componentChunkName":"component---src-layouts-blog-post-layout-js","path":"/blog/craft-theme-add-arrows-to-zoom-images","result":{"pageContext":{"id":1628,"date":"2022-04-23T22:34:58","date_gmt":"2022-04-23T22:34:58","guid":{"rendered":"https://www.ezfy.club/?p=1628"},"modified":"2022-04-23T22:47:03","modified_gmt":"2022-04-23T22:47:03","slug":"craft-theme-add-arrows-to-zoom-images","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https://www.ezfy.club/craft-theme-add-arrows-to-zoom-images/","title":{"rendered":"Craft theme: add arrows to zoom images (mobile &#038; desktop)"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>The Craft theme ships with a &#8220;click-to-zoom&#8221; button which allows users to view an enlarged version of the product images.<br><br>Although helpful, these images often get cut off especially on mobile devices. In this tutorial I&#8217;ll quickly teach you how you can not only fix the size of the zoomed images size, but also add arrows to it so your users can have a more pleasant experience when viewing your product&#8217;s images.<br><br>This is how the final result will look like: <a href=\"https://snippets-password-is-123.myshopify.com/products/ezfy-zoom\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">live preview</a>. (password: <strong>123)</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Making a backup of your theme</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Before diving into the tutorial make sure you download the theme, so in case you face any issues you can easily revert back.<br><br><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1514\" height=\"481\" class=\"wp-image-503\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123.png 1514w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123-600x191.png 600w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123-1200x381.png 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123-768x244.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1514px) 100vw, 1514px\" /></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-downloading-the-code-files\">Downloading the code files</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You can download the code files <a href=\"https://ezfycode.com/shop/craft-theme-zoom-slider-pro\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">clicking here</a>. (<a href=\"https://snippets-password-is-123.myshopify.com/products/ezfy-zoom\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">live preview</a>)</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-copying-the-code\">Copying the code</h3>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>In your Shopify admin, go to <strong>Online Store</strong> > <strong>Themes </strong>> <strong>Actions </strong>> <strong>Edit Code</strong>.</li><li>Inside the <a href=\"https://ezfycode.com/shop/craft-theme-zoom-slider-pro\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">.zip you downloaded</a> you&#8217;ll find the following file: <br><strong>ezfy-zoom.txt</strong></li></ol>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-creating-the-code-file\">Creating the code file</h3>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>Open the <strong>ezfy-zoom.txt </strong>file and copy all the code in there.</li><li>Now go back to your Shopify code editor and below <strong>Snippets</strong> click on &#8220;<em>Add a new snippet</em>&#8220;. <br><br>Name it exactly: <strong>ezfy-zoom</strong><br><br><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1401\" height=\"698\" class=\"wp-image-894\" style=\"width: 650px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom1.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom1.png 1401w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom1-600x299.png 600w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom1-1200x598.png 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom1-768x383.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1401px) 100vw, 1401px\" /><br></li><li>Paste the code that you copied and click on <strong>save</strong>.<br><br><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1564\" height=\"438\" class=\"wp-image-896\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom-2.jpg 1564w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom-2-600x168.jpg 600w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom-2-1200x336.jpg 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom-2-768x215.jpg 768w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom-2-1536x430.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1564px) 100vw, 1564px\" /></li></ol>\n\n\n\n<h3>Final step: adding the code to your theme</h3>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>Find the file named <strong>theme.liquid</strong>.</li><li>Inside this file, press CTRL + F (or CMD + F on Mac) and search for:<br><br><strong>&lt;/body&gt;</strong></li><li>Paste the following code&nbsp;<strong>before&nbsp;</strong>the&nbsp;<strong>&lt;/body&gt;</strong>&nbsp;tag you found and save:<br><br><code>{% include 'ezfy-zoom' %}</code></li></ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"720\" height=\"698\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-898\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom-3.jpg 720w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom-3-600x582.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>That is it! You&#8217;re all set. You can now test the new zoom by simply clicking on the magnifying glass icon of any of your product page images.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-container-5 wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\"></div></div>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Easily fix your Craft&#8217;s theme lightbox zoom images&#8217; width and height by copying and pasting one single piece of code.  </p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":1631,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[9],"tags":[626],"image_alt